Wide Canyons & Ridges Prevailing wind direction can be altered by the direction of a wide canyon, but cross-canyon spotting is not common except in high winds. General fire conditions will differ greatly between north and south aspects. Fires burning along lateral ridges may change direction at a point where the ridge drops off into a canyon due to the airflow in the canyon.
